Memory Map
---
- 0x0000 - 0x5FFF   : RAM
  - 0x0000 - 0x00FF : Stack
  - 0x0100 - 0x5FFF : RAM
- 0x6000 - 0x6401   : Storage
  - 0x6000          : Bank select (64 bank loops after 64)
  - 0x6001 - 0x6400 : 1024 bytes * bank
- 0x6401 - 0x6FFF   : Unused
- 0x7000 - 0xFFFD   : ROM
- 0xFFFE - 0xFFFF   : Reset Vector

Instructions
---
- A Register Manipulation
  - 0x01 : LDA (immediate)
    - Load A register with operand
  - 0x02 : LDA (address)
    - Load A register from address specified from two operands
  - 0x03 : STA
    - Stores A register at location specified from two operands
  - 0x04 : ADA
    - Adds operand to A register
  - 0x05 : SBA
    - Subtracts operand from A register
  - 0x06 : PSA
    - Pushes A register to stack
  - 0x07 : PLA
    - Pulls from the stack to the A register
- X Register Manipulation
  - 0x11 : LDX (immediate)
    - Load X register with operand
  - 0x12 : LDX (address)
    - Load X register from address specified from two operands
  - 0x13 : STX
    - Stores X register at location specified from two operands
  - 0x14 : ADX
    - Adds operand to X register
  - 0x15 : SBX
    - Subtracts operand from X register
  - 0x16 : PSX
    - Pushes X register to stack
  - 0x17 : PLX
    - Pulls from the stack to the X register
- Y Register Manipulation
  - 0x21 : LDY (immediate)
    - Load Y register with operand
  - 0x22 : LDY (address)
    - Load Y register from address specified from two operands
  - 0x23 : STY
    - Stores Y register at location specified from two operands
  - 0x24 : ADY
    - Adds operand to Y register
  - 0x25 : SBY
    - Subtracts operand from Y register
  - 0x26 : PSY
    - Pushes Y register to stack
  - 0x27 : PLY
    - Pulls from the stack to the Y register
- Flow Control
  - 0x00 : NOP
    - No Operation
  - 0x30 : JMP
    - Jumps the PC to the location specified by two operands
  - 0x31 : JXZ
    - Similar to the JMP instruction except it only jumps when X is zero
  - 0x32 : JYZ
    - Similar to the JMP instruction except it only jumps when Y is zero
  - 0x33 : JSR
    - Pushes PC to stack and jumps to subroutine 
  - 0x34 : RSR
    - Pops PC from stack and returns from subroutine